{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8088"},"text":"§ 8088.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Judge Advocate General’s Corps: Office of the Judge Advocate General; Judge Advocate General; appointment, term, emoluments, duties","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Judge Advocate General’s Corps is a Staff Corps of the Navy, and shall be organized in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Secretary of the Navy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There is in the executive part of the Department of the Navy the Office of the Judge Advocate General of the Navy. The Judge Advocate General shall be appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, for a term of four years. He shall be appointed from judge advocates of the Navy or the Marine Corps who are members of the bar of a Federal court or the highest court of a State and who have had at least eight years of experience in legal duties as commissioned officers.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Under regulations prescribed by the Secretary of Defense, the Secretary of the Navy, in selecting an officer for recommendation to the President for appointment as the Judge Advocate General, shall ensure that the officer selected is recommended by a board of officers that, insofar as practicable, is subject to the procedures applicable to selection boards convened under chapter 36 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Judge Advocate General of the Navy, under the direction of the Secretary of the Navy, shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" perform duties relating to legal matters arising in the Department of the Navy as may be assigned to him;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2de9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" perform the functions and duties and exercise the powers prescribed for the Judge Advocate General in chapter 47 of this title;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2dea-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" receive, revise, and have recorded the proceedings of boards for the examination of officers of the naval service for promotion and retirement; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2deb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" perform such other duties as may be assigned to him.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2dec-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" No officer or employee of the Department of Defense may interfere with—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2ded-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the ability of the Judge Advocate General to give independent legal advice to the Secretary of the Navy or the Chief of Naval Operations; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2dee-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the ability of judge advocates of the Navy assigned or attached to, or performing duty with, military units to give independent legal advice to commanders.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2def-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8088/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If the Judge Advocate General is removed from office before the end of the term of the Judge Advocate General as specified in subsection (b), the Secretary of Defense shall, not later than five days after the removal takes effect, submit to the Committees on Armed Services of the Senate and the House of Representatives notice that the Judge Advocate General is being removed and a statement of the reason for the removal.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab0e2df0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/289"},"text":"70A Stat. 289","children":[],"tail":", § 5148; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/649/s14c/20"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–649, § 14c(20)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-09-07"},"text":"Sept. 7, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/501"},"text":"76 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/179/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–179, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/546"},"text":"81 Stat. 546","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/tIII/s343"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, title III, § 343","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2901"},"text":"94 Stat. 2901","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tV/s504/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title V, § 504(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2750"},"text":"108 Stat. 2750","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tV/s574/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title V, § 574(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1922"},"text":"118 Stat. 1922","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/dA/tV/s508/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, div. A, title V, § 508(b)","children":[],"tail":", title X, § 1057(a)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/3229"},"text":"119 Stat. 3229","children":[],"tail":", 3440; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/dA/tV/s543/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, div. A, title V, § 543(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-28"},"text":"Jan. 28, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/115"},"text":"122 Stat. 115","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/dA/tV/s502/ff"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328, div. A, title V, § 502(ff)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/2105"},"text":"130 Stat. 2105","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 8088, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s807/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 807(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1834"},"text":"132 Stat. 1834","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dA/tV/s506/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. A, title V, § 506(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/858"},"text":"139 Stat. 858","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab0e2df1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab0e2df2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idab0e2df3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"5148","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s428"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 428","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1880-06-08/ch129"},"text":"June 8, 1880, ch. 129","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/21/164"},"text":"21 Stat. 164","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1896-06-05/ch331"},"text":"June 5, 1896, ch. 331","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/29/251"},"text":"29 Stat. 251","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s741"},"text":"50 U.S.C. 741","children":[],"tail":" (as applicable to Navy JAG)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-05-05/ch169/s13"},"text":"May 5, 1950, ch. 169, § 13","children":[],"tail":" (as applicable to Navy JAG), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/147"},"text":"64 Stat. 147","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s441"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 441","children":[],"tail":" (as applicable to JAG)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1918-07-01/ch114"},"text":"July 1, 1918, ch. 114","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/717"},"text":"40 Stat. 717","children":[],"tail":" (1st sentence on p. 717, as applicable to JAG)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s425a"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 425a","children":[],"tail":" (as applicable to JAG)."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-22/ch567"},"text":"June 22, 1938, ch. 567","children":[],"tail":" (as applicable to JAG), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/839"},"text":"52 Stat. 839","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b) the rank, pay, allowances, and privileges of retirement of chiefs of bureaus of the Navy are incorporated. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s441"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 441","children":[],"tail":" apparently relates the Judge Advocate General of the Navy to the Judge Advocate General of the Army, as well as to bureau chiefs. However, since the creation of the Department of the Air Force by the National Security Act of 1947, if the incorporation to the Army provision is retained, the saving provisions in the act require an incorporation also to the rank, etc., of the Judge Advocate General of the Air Force. The rank of the Judge Advocate General of each of the other departments is now specified in organizational law to be major general. Since it is possible that these ranks may at some future time not be the same, incorporation by reference to them is no longer appropriate. Instead, the section relates the Judge Advocate General’s rank, pay, allowances, and privileges of retirement to those of bureau chiefs as does "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s441"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 441","children":[],"tail":", in part."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), clauses (1) and (4) are substituted for the words “and perform such other duties as have heretofore been performed by the Solicitor and Naval Judge Advocate General” to describe the duties of the Judge Advocate General directly instead of by reference to the duties performed by an officer whose office was abolished more than 75 years ago.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (c)(2) is substituted for the reference, in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s428"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 428","children":[],"tail":", to courts-martial and courts of inquiry, since the Uniform Code of Military Justice has superseded prior law as to the duties of the Judge Advocates General relating to these courts."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab0e2df4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab0e2df5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s5148"},"text":"section 5148 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328","children":[],"tail":" struck out last sentence which read as follows: “The Judge Advocate General, while so serving, has the grade of vice admiral or lieutenant general, as appropriate.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181","children":[],"tail":" substituted “The Judge Advocate General, while so serving, has the grade of vice admiral or lieutenant general, as appropriate.” for “The Judge Advocate General, while so serving, shall hold a grade not lower than rear admiral or major general, as appropriate.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s1057/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 1057(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “or Territory” after “highest court of a State”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s508/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 508(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “The Judge Advocate General, while so serving, shall hold a grade not lower than rear admiral or major general, as appropriate.” for “If an officer appointed as the Judge Advocate General holds a lower regular grade, the officer shall be appointed in the regular grade of rear admiral or major general, as appropriate.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s504/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 504(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", added last sentence and struck out former last sentence which read as follows: “While so serving, the Judge Advocate General of the Navy shall be entitled to the rank and grade of rear admiral or major general, as appropriate, unless entitled to a higher rank and grade under another provision of law.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s504/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 504(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c) and struck out former subsec. (c) which read as follows: “The Judge Advocate General of the Navy is entitled to the same rank and privileges of retirement as provided for chiefs of bureaus in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s5133"},"text":"section 5133 of this title","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":" inserted provision entitling Judge Advocate General of Navy to rank and grade of rear admiral or major general, as appropriate."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1967—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/179/s2/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–179, § 2(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted reference to Judge Advocate General’s Corps in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (a) to (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/179/s2/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–179, § 2(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (C), added subsec. (a), redesignated existing subsecs. (a) to (c) as (b) to (d), respectively, and in subsec. (b) as so redesignated substituted “judge advocates” for “officers”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1962—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/649"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–649","children":[],"tail":" struck out “, pay, allowances,” after “same rank”. See Title 37, Pay and Allowances of the Uniformed Services."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab0e2df6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab0e2df7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-02-01"},"text":"Feb. 1, 2019","children":[],"tail":", with provision for the coordination of amendments and special rule for certain redesignations, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s800"},"text":"section 800 of Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab0e2df8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-09-15"},"text":"Sept. 15, 1981","children":[],"tail":", but the authority to prescribe regulations under the amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":" effective on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s701"},"text":"section 701 of Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab0e2df9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1962 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/649"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–649","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1962","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/649/s15"},"text":"section 15 of Pub. L. 87–649","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 37","children":[],"tail":", Pay and Allowances of the Uniformed Services."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idab0e2dfa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Redesignation of Navy Law Specialists as Judge Advocates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/179/s8"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–179, § 8","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/549"},"text":"81 Stat. 549","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/90/179/s8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In this section ‘law specialist’ means a line officer on the active or retired list of the Regular Navy or of the Naval Reserve designated for special duty (law) or a line officer of the Naval Reserve [now Navy Reserve] assigned a numerical designator indicating a special duty officer (law).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" All law specialists in the Navy are redesignated as judge advocates in the Judge Advocate General’s Corps of the Navy. Each law specialist of the Navy who is on a promotion list on the day before the effective date of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1967","children":[],"tail":"] shall be placed on the appropriate promotion list for the Judge Advocate General’s Corps and shall be eligible for promotion when the officer who is to be his running mate in the next higher grade becomes eligible for promotion in that grade.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"savings","id":"idab0e2dfb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Savings Provision","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/179/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–179, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/549"},"text":"81 Stat. 549","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/90/179/s10"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 5578a and 5587a of this title, amending this section, sections 801, 806, 815, 827, 865, 936, 5149, 5404, 5508, 5581, 5587, 5600, 5652a, 5702, 5708, 5753, 5762, 5896, 5897 and 6378 of this title, and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s202"},"text":"section 202 of Title 37","children":[],"tail":", and enacting provisions set out as notes under this section and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s5149"},"text":"section 5149 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] does not affect rights accrued, duties matured, or proceedings commenced before its effective date. Redesignation of an officer under section 8(b) of this Act [set out as a note under this section] shall not operate to change the computation of his service for any purpose.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
